{"review":{"checks":{"evidence_quotes":"mixed","metadata":"fail","numeric_claims":"mixed","schema":"pass","semantic_grounding":"mixed","taxonomy_mapping":"pass"},"confidence":"high","field_reviews":[{"field":"research_purpose","paper_evidence":"In this article, we propose a RISC-V CPU/NPU co-computing-based compilation framework to solve the problem of mapping from algorithms to heterogeneous architectures.","reason":"该字段与摘要和引言一致，准确概括了论文目标，没有明显外推。","severity":"minor","status":"supported","suggested_fix":"保持不变"},{"field":"research_significance","paper_evidence":"Despite this potential, there is currently insufficient academic focus on CPU/NPU co-computing, and few architectures or toolchains have been developed to support such integration.","reason":"总体方向正确，但“填补空白”“通用的、可配置的CNN异构部署方案”等表述略强于原文。论文强调学术关注不足和支持多种CNN，但未直接宣称“填补空白”。","severity":"minor","status":"partially_supported","suggested_fix":"改为更保守表述：该工作面向RISC-V CPU/NPU协同编译这一研究较少的方向，基于ONNX-MLIR实现多种CNN的异构映射与优化，并在代码密度和内存使用上取得提升。"},{"field":"contributions","paper_evidence":"1) By extending the ONNX-MLIR framework with custom operators, we introduce an operator packing technique that maximizes the computational efficiency of NPUs, while minimizing overhead during transitions between heterogeneous operations. 2) A task scheduler with three operational modes is developed, allowing users to customize the task distribution according to specific requirements, including correctness verification, performance optimization, or detailed analysis of computational workflows across heterogeneous platforms, which typically emphasizes the versatility of the framework. 3) The discrete memory allocation strategy is optimized to accommodate the CPU/NPU heterogeneous architecture, ensuring seamless data access during cross-platform computations. To further enhance memory efficiency, the memory management system incorporates two techniques: a dual-end (DE) allocation strategy with a self-check function, and a release-after-use (RU) mechanism that minimizes memory footprint.","reason":"贡献点总体与论文一致。第二条 evidence 不是完全逐字匹配，但与正文贡献列表高度一致，可保守修正为论文中的精确引文。","severity":"minor","status":"partially_supported","suggested_fix":"保留四个贡献点的结构，但将第二条 evidence 改为论文贡献列表中的原句；第四条贡献可继续保留，但措辞应避免夸大“弥合差距”的结论强度。"},{"field":"theme_primary","paper_evidence":"The ONNX-MLIR toolchain [10] is a modular, open-source framework that supports adaptive scaling, converting ONNX input into multilevel intermediate representations (MLIRs). However, it currently lacks support for generating back-end instructions for heterogeneous architectures.","reason":"论文核心是基于ONNX-MLIR的异构编译框架，主主题归类为编译器/IR/算子生成是合理的。","severity":"minor","status":"supported","suggested_fix":"保持不变"},{"field":"theme_secondary","paper_evidence":"RISC-V reserves signiﬁcant instruction code space for user-\ndeﬁned extensions [6], [7], making it ideal for domain-speciﬁc\nenhancements.","reason":"论文确实涉及RISC-V自定义指令空间和NPU指令映射，因此次主题归入RISC-V custom ISA合理。","severity":"minor","status":"supported","suggested_fix":"保持不变"},{"field":"workstream_fit","paper_evidence":"Different hardware architectures often have their own unique instruction sets and capabilities. To integrate a heterogeneous compilation platform that supports multiple architectures, it is essential to ensure that the generated code is compatible across all targeted devices.","reason":"论文更偏向RISC-V ISA与编译器协同，而非CPU核内矩阵扩展或系统级HBM，因此映射到工作流2合理。","severity":"minor","status":"supported","suggested_fix":"保持不变"},{"field":"is_close_baseline_to_cute","paper_evidence":"However, these architectures often support only a limited number of CNNs and uses the CPU solely as a host, without incorporating it into the computation process.","reason":"该论文不是CPU矩阵扩展、核内AI加速器或直接的CUTE基线，设置为 false 合理。","severity":"minor","status":"supported","suggested_fix":"保持不变"},{"field":"key_technique","paper_evidence":"To ensure compatibility within a heterogeneous archi-\ntecture, each 512-bit NPU instruction must be split into\n18 individual 32-bit instructions in the RISC-V format.","reason":"技术路线总体准确，包含自定义算子、算法适配、数据协调、量化和权重重排等要点。少量实现细节属于综合表述，但未发现核心性失真。","severity":"minor","status":"supported","suggested_fix":"保持不变，必要时将“无缝集成”等评价性措辞弱化为“实现映射与兼容”"},{"field":"key_results","paper_evidence":"It achieves up to a 7.06× reduction in code density and up to a 5.58× improvement in memory usage. For example, ResNet50 requires only 1.97 MB, achieving a 5.58× reduction compared to SS. In comparison to other architectures listed in the table, such as the extended SODA synthesizer in [14], our architecture excels in delivering lower memory footprints (e.g., 24.4 MB for ResNet50 compared to 97.7 MB in [14]) and reduced latency (e.g., 56.7 ms for ResNet50 compared to 1614.8 ms in [14]) even converted to 32-bit precision. All_CPU Mode: In this mode, we run YOLOv3-Tiny with an input size of 224 × 224 × 3 (in 8-bit), and observed an extraordinarily high cycle count of 277 billion cycles.","reason":"主要结果基本有据，但原文把 ResNet50 与 [14] 的对比内存写为 24.4 MB 对 97.7 MB，而分析稿写成 11.00 MB 对 97.7 MB，混淆了不同比较口径；“2770亿周期”虽语义接近 277 billion cycles，但不宜作为纸面精确摘录。","severity":"major","status":"partially_supported","suggested_fix":"将结果改写为：代码密度最高降低 7.06×、DE 相比 SS 的内存使用最高改善 5.58×；ResNet50 在 DE 下为 1.97 MB，在与 [14] 的对比中延迟为 56.7 ms 对 1614.8 ms、内存为 24.4 MB 对 97.7 MB；ALL_CPU 模式下 YOLOv3-Tiny 观测到 277 billion cycles。"},{"field":"gap_identified","paper_evidence":"Moving forward, we could explore the integration of more\nadvanced machine learning models, such as transformers, and\ntheir adaptation to more heterogeneous architectures. In our work, we chose to use discrete memory allocation. While this approach can be more complex to manage because it requires explicit data transfers between the memory of CPU and the memory of NPU, it can offer more control. One reason for this high cycle count may be that the RV32IM ISA lacks the specialized hardware extensions needed for efﬁcient deep learning workloads. Based on the above analysis, there are two key approaches for our architecture to enhance the CPU inference speed. First, we can customize the instruction set for deep learning tasks; second, a larger cache is needed.","reason":"第1和第3个 gap 有文本支持。第2个 gap 的原 evidence 不是逐字引文，而是把两段话拼接并加了省略，需改成论文中的直接引文。","severity":"major","status":"partially_supported","suggested_fix":"保留三个 gap 的方向，但将第2条 evidence 替换为论文中的精确句子；同时把“关键路径”等提炼语气收敛为“为CUTE提供动机/启发”。"},{"field":"proposal_evidence.for_state_of_art","paper_evidence":"The ONNX-MLIR toolchain [10] is a modular, open-source framework that supports adaptive scaling, converting ONNX input into multilevel intermediate representations (MLIRs). However, it currently lacks support for generating back-end instructions for heterogeneous architectures.","reason":"该字段将论文定位为基于MLIR的较新异构编译工作，这一判断基本成立；但“前沿工作”属于推断，应保持谨慎。","severity":"minor","status":"partially_supported","suggested_fix":"改为较保守表述：该论文代表了基于 ONNX-MLIR 扩展异构后端指令生成的一项近期工作，可作为RISC-V异构编译现状的参考。"},{"field":"proposal_evidence.for_gap","paper_evidence":"All_CPU Mode: In this mode, we run YOLOv3-Tiny with an input size of 224 × 224 × 3 (in 8-bit), and observed an extraordinarily high cycle count of 277 billion cycles. One reason for this high cycle count may be that the RV32IM ISA lacks the specialized hardware extensions needed for efﬁcient deep learning workloads. Based on the above analysis, there are two key approaches for our architecture to enhance the CPU inference speed. First, we can customize the instruction set for deep learning tasks; second, a larger cache is needed. However, these architectures often support only a limited number of CNNs and uses the CPU solely as a host, without incorporating it into the computation process. Moving forward, we could explore the integration of more advanced machine learning models, such as transformers, and their adaptation to more heterogeneous architectures.","reason":"论证方向基本成立，但原文把多个观察提升为对CUTE的系统性支撑，存在轻度外推。尤其“系统性解决方案”不是论文原文结论。","severity":"minor","status":"partially_supported","suggested_fix":"改成“这些观察为CUTE关于CPU扩展、编译支持和模型覆盖面的设计提供动机”，避免写成论文直接证明CUTE方案。"},{"field":"proposal_evidence.for_feasibility","paper_evidence":"To ensure compatibility within a heterogeneous archi-\ntecture, each 512-bit NPU instruction must be split into\n18 individual 32-bit instructions in the RISC-V format. For example, ResNet50 requires only 1.97 MB, achieving a 5.58× reduction compared to SS. In comparison to other architectures listed in the table, such as the extended SODA synthesizer in [14], our architecture excels in delivering lower memory footprints (e.g., 24.4 MB for ResNet50 compared to 97.7 MB in [14]) and reduced latency (e.g., 56.7 ms for ResNet50 compared to 1614.8 ms in [14]) even converted to 32-bit precision.","reason":"第1和第2点有据。第3点中的“28.5倍加速”无法从论文文本中直接验证，属于过度推导；文中只明确给出 56.7 ms 对 1614.8 ms 的对比。","severity":"major","status":"partially_supported","suggested_fix":"删除“28.5倍加速”表述，改为引用论文明确给出的延迟和内存数据，并把可行性结论限定为“说明低精度与编译器/内存协同优化在该平台上有效”。"}],"issues":[{"field":"title","paper_evidence":"A Heterogeneous CNN Compilation Framework for RISC-V CPU and NPU Integration Based on ONNX-MLIR","problem":"标题与源论文不一致，分析稿使用了中文改写标题而非论文原题。","recommended_action":"将 `title` 改为论文原始英文标题。","severity":"critical"},{"field":"contributions[1].evidence","paper_evidence":"A task scheduler with three operational modes is developed, allowing users to customize the task distribution according to specific requirements, including correctness verification, performance optimization, or detailed analysis of computational workflows across heterogeneous platforms, which typically emphasizes the versatility of the framework.","problem":"证据引文不是逐字原文，末尾被改写为更流畅的总结句。","recommended_action":"替换为论文贡献列表中的精确英文原句。","severity":"minor"},{"field":"gap_identified[1].evidence","paper_evidence":"One reason for this high cycle count may be that the RV32IM ISA lacks the specialized hardware extensions needed for efﬁcient deep learning workloads. Based on the above analysis, there are two key approaches for our architecture to enhance the CPU inference speed. First, we can customize the instruction set for deep learning tasks; second, a larger cache is needed.","problem":"原 evidence 使用了带省略号的拼接句，不是论文中的直接英文引文。","recommended_action":"改用论文中的完整直接引文，避免省略号和自造连接。","severity":"major"},{"field":"gap_identified[2].evidence","paper_evidence":"In our work, we chose to use discrete memory allocation. While this approach can be more complex to manage because it requires explicit data transfers between the memory of CPU and the memory of NPU, it can offer more control.","problem":"证据接近原文，但顺序和断句与论文不完全一致。","recommended_action":"替换为论文中的精确两句原文。","severity":"minor"},{"field":"key_results","paper_evidence":"In comparison to other architectures listed in the table, such as the extended SODA synthesizer in [14], our architecture excels in delivering lower memory footprints (e.g., 24.4 MB for ResNet50 compared to 97.7 MB in [14]) and reduced latency (e.g., 56.7 ms for ResNet50 compared to 1614.8 ms in [14]) even converted to 32-bit precision.","problem":"分析稿把 ResNet50 与 [14] 的比较内存写成 11.00MB 对 97.7MB，混淆了 SS/DE 内部比较与跨论文比较。","recommended_action":"分别写清两类结果：DE 对 SS 为 1.97 MB 对 11.00 MB；与 [14] 对比为 24.4 MB 对 97.7 MB、56.7 ms 对 1614.8 ms。","severity":"major"},{"field":"proposal_evidence.for_feasibility","paper_evidence":"信息不足，无法从文本中提取","problem":"“相比32-bit实现（1614.8ms）有28.5倍加速”这一数值关系无法从论文文本中直接成立；1614.8 ms 来自与文献 [14] 的对比，不是同一实现的 32-bit 基线。","recommended_action":"删除 28.5 倍加速说法，改用论文直接给出的延迟与内存数据。","severity":"major"}],"overall_verdict":"major_revision","ready_for_proposal_use":false,"review_target":{"analysis_json_path":"/root/opencute/workspace/survey/data/topics/cpu-ai/corpus/llm/glm5.1/A-Heterogeneous-CNN-Compilation-Framework-for-RISC-V-CPU-and-NPU-Integration-Bas.json","analysis_title":"一种基于ONNX-MLIR的面向RISC-V CPU与NPU集成的异构CNN编译框架","paper_json_path":"/root/opencute/workspace/survey/data/topics/cpu-ai/corpus/draft/A-Heterogeneous-CNN-Compilation-Framework-for-RISC-V-CPU-and-NPU-Integration-Bas.json","paper_title":"A Heterogeneous CNN Compilation Framework for RISC-V CPU and NPU Integration Based on ONNX-MLIR","resolved_paper_by":"explicit_path"},"stats":{"matched_evidence_quotes":4,"matched_numeric_claims":23,"missing_required_fields":[],"required_field_count":17,"total_evidence_quotes":7,"total_numeric_claims":25},"summary":"该分析稿整体抓住了论文主线，主题归类和多数技术要点基本可信，但存在一个关键元数据错误、至少一处非逐字证据引文，以及若干结果数字口径混淆。最主要的问题是标题未与源论文一致、第二个 gap 的 evidence 不是论文原句、以及将内部内存比较与跨论文比较混写。修正后可继续用于提案参考，但当前版本还不适合直接下游使用。"},"revised_analysis":{"authors":"Shan Cao, Meiling Yang, Yintao Liu, Yu Li, Beining Zhao, Xinyu Chen, Zhiyuan Jiang","contributions":[{"evidence":"By extending the ONNX-MLIR framework with custom operators, we introduce an operator packing technique that maximizes the computational efficiency of NPUs, while minimizing overhead during transitions between heterogeneous operations.","point":"提出算子打包技术，通过扩展 ONNX-MLIR 的自定义算子，将多个 CNN 操作组合映射到 NPU，以减少异构操作切换开销并提升 NPU 计算效率。"},{"evidence":"A task scheduler with three operational modes is developed, allowing users to customize the task distribution according to specific requirements, including correctness verification, performance optimization, or detailed analysis of computational workflows across heterogeneous platforms, which typically emphasizes the versatility of the framework.","point":"开发了三模式任务调度器，支持按照正确性验证、性能优化或异构工作流分析需求定制 CPU/NPU 任务分配。"},{"evidence":"The discrete memory allocation strategy is optimized to accommodate the CPU/NPU heterogeneous architecture, ensuring seamless data access during cross-platform computations. To further enhance memory efficiency, the memory management system incorporates two techniques: a dual-end (DE) allocation strategy with a self-check function, and a release-after-use (RU) mechanism that minimizes memory footprint.","point":"提出面向 CPU/NPU 异构架构的内存管理优化，包括带自检的 DE 分配策略和 RU 机制，以保证跨平台数据访问正确性并降低内存占用。"},{"evidence":"To bridge the computational gap between heterogeneous platforms, within ONNX-MLIR, we developed three phases to support operator packing, algorithm adaption, and data coordination.","point":"在 ONNX-MLIR 中实现了面向异构平台的三阶段编译流程，覆盖算子打包、算法适配与数据协调。"}],"doi":"10.1109/TCAD.2025.3564561","gap_identified":[{"evidence":"Moving forward, we could explore the integration of more\nadvanced machine learning models, such as transformers, and\ntheir adaptation to more heterogeneous architectures.","gap":"该框架当前聚焦 CNN，论文将 Transformer 等更先进模型的集成留作未来工作，说明模型覆盖面仍有限。","relevance_to_cute":"这对 CUTE 的启发在于：若希望支持更广泛的 AI 工作负载，仅靠 CNN 导向的异构编译策略还不够，需进一步考虑矩阵/张量算力扩展与更通用算子支持。"},{"evidence":"One reason for this high cycle count may be that the RV32IM ISA lacks the specialized hardware extensions needed for efﬁcient deep learning workloads. Based on the above analysis, there are two key approaches for our architecture to enhance the CPU inference speed. First, we can customize the instruction set for deep learning tasks; second, a larger cache is needed.","gap":"所用 RV32IM CPU 缺少适合深度学习的专用扩展，纯 CPU 推理代价很高；论文明确指出可通过定制指令集和更大 cache 提升速度。","relevance_to_cute":"这为 CUTE 的 CPU 侧矩阵/张量扩展与片上存储优化提供了直接动机，说明 CPU 端 ISA 与内存层次是瓶颈所在。"},{"evidence":"In our work, we chose to use discrete memory allocation. While this approach can be more complex to manage because it requires explicit data transfers between the memory of CPU and the memory of NPU, it can offer more control.","gap":"论文采用离散式内存分配，CPU 与 NPU 之间需要显式数据传输，这增加了系统管理复杂度并可能带来传输开销。","relevance_to_cute":"这对 CUTE 的意义在于：如果在 CPU 侧引入矩阵加速能力，仍需同步考虑片上数据流、scratchpad 与访存组织，否则异构协同会受到数据搬运成本限制。"}],"is_close_baseline_to_cute":false,"key_results":"论文报告该框架可将代码密度最高降低 7.06×，并将内存使用最高改善 5.58×。在内存管理实验中，ResNet50 的 FM 内存从 SS 的 11.00 MB 降至 DE 的 1.97 MB。与文献 [14] 对比时，论文给出 ResNet50 的内存占用为 24.4 MB 对 97.7 MB、延迟为 56.7 ms 对 1614.8 ms；在 ALL_CPU 模式下，YOLOv3-Tiny（224 × 224 × 3, 8-bit）观测到 277 billion cycles，显示 RV32IM CPU 处理深度学习工作负载时开销很高。","key_technique":"核心技术是基于 ONNX-MLIR 构建面向 RISC-V CPU/NPU 协同计算的异构编译流程：在 ONNX dialect 中增加自定义算子以实现算子打包；通过 padding、reshaping 和数据布局调整完成算法适配与数据协调；引入任务调度、权重量化、权重重排和内存管理等附加功能；并将每条 512-bit NPU 指令拆分为 18 条 32-bit RISC-V 格式指令，以实现异构后端指令生成与兼容。","proposal_evidence":{"for_feasibility":"论文提供了三类与可行性相关的证据。首先，论文明确展示了如何把每条 512-bit NPU 指令拆分为 18 条 32-bit RISC-V 格式指令，说明在 RISC-V 指令框架内承载异构加速器控制是可实现的。其次，DE 内存管理在 ResNet50 上把 FM 内存降到 1.97 MB，相比 SS 达到 5.58× 改善，说明编译器与内存策略协同优化可以显著提升资源效率。再次，论文给出了与既有工作相比的延迟和内存优势，例如 ResNet50 为 56.7 ms 对 1614.8 ms、24.4 MB 对 97.7 MB，这表明该类异构编译与低精度部署路线在边缘 AI 平台上具备工程可行性。","for_gap":"论文揭示了几个与后续研究相关的不足。其一，ALL_CPU 模式下 YOLOv3-Tiny 需要 277 billion cycles，且作者指出 RV32IM 缺少适合深度学习的专用扩展，并提出可通过定制指令集与更大 cache 提升 CPU 推理速度。其二，论文回顾的异构体系大多把 CPU 作为主机而不是计算参与者，限制了通用性。其三，论文将 Transformer 等更先进模型的集成列为未来工作，表明当前框架仍以 CNN 为主。这些观察可以作为 CUTE 在 CPU 扩展、编译支持和模型覆盖面方面的动机依据。","for_state_of_art":"该论文发表于 2025 年 IEEE-TCAD，代表了一项基于 ONNX-MLIR 扩展异构后端指令生成的近期工作。它展示了如何把开源 MLIR 工具链扩展到 RISC-V CPU/NPU 协同编译场景，并结合任务调度、量化、权重重排和内存管理完成 CNN 部署。与此同时，论文所用 CPU 仍是 RV32IM 基础 ISA，说明 RISC-V 面向 AI 的专用 ISA 与体系结构增强仍有明显提升空间。"},"research_purpose":"针对 RISC-V CPU 与 NPU 异构平台上的 CNN 推理部署问题，论文提出一个基于 ONNX-MLIR 的编译框架，用于解决从算法到异构体系结构的映射与编译问题。该框架通过算子打包、任务调度、量化、权重重排和内存管理等机制支持 CPU 与 NPU 协同计算。","research_significance":"该工作面向学术关注相对不足的 CPU/NPU 协同编译方向，扩展了 ONNX-MLIR 对异构后端指令生成的支持，并展示了多种 CNN 在 RISC-V CPU/NPU 平台上的部署流程。论文实验表明，该框架在代码密度和内存使用方面可取得明显改进，为后续研究异构编译、RISC-V 扩展和边缘 AI 部署提供了参考。","theme_primary":"7. Compiler / tensor IR / operator generation","theme_secondary":"4. RISC-V custom ISA / open ISA AI extension","title":"A Heterogeneous CNN Compilation Framework for RISC-V CPU and NPU Integration Based on ONNX-MLIR","venue":"IEEE-TCAD","workstream_fit":"2","year":2025}}
